Definition:
	Loops allow you to run the same code multiple times. Useful for repeating commands, or iterating through lists.

Types:
	for:
		used when the number of iterations is known
	while:
		used when the number of iterations is unknown
	do-while:
		similar to the while. The code executes at least once.

Syntax:
	for ( var declaration; condition; increment )

	while ( condition ) {

	}

	do {

	} while ( condition );
